name: The number of non-unitary prime divisors of the biquadratefree numbers.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000

Sourabhashis Das, Wentang Kuo, and Yu-Ru Liu, On the number of prime factors with a given multiplicity over h-free and h-full numbers, Journal of Number Theory, Vol. 267 (2025), pp. 176-201; arXiv preprint, arXiv:2409.11275 [math.NT], 2024. See Theorem 1.2.
formula: Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ c * n, where c = Sum_{p prime} (1/(p^2+1)) = 0.38905955531696837... - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 25 2025 (according to the above formula)
mathematica: f[k_] := Module[{e = If[k == 1, {}, FactorInteger[k][[;; , 2]]]}, If[AllTrue[e, # < 4 &], Count[e, _?(# > 1 &)], Nothing]]; Array[f, 150]
program: (PARI) list(kmax) = {my(e, is); for(k = 1, kmax, e = factor(k)[, 2]; is = 1; for(i = 1, #e, if(e[i] > 3, is = 0; break)); if(is, print1(#select(x -> x > 1, e), ", "))); }
author: _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 25 2025

name: The number of exponents in the prime factorization of n-th biquadratefree number that are equal to 2.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000

Sourabhashis Das, Wentang Kuo, and Yu-Ru Liu, On the number of prime factors with a given multiplicity over h-free and h-full numbers, Journal of Number Theory, Vol. 267 (2025), pp. 176-201; arXiv preprint, arXiv:2409.11275 [math.NT], 2024. See Theorem 1.2.
formula: Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ c * n, where c = Sum_{p prime} (p*(p-1)/(p^4-1)) = 0.28680338438307129... - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 25 2025 (according to the above formula)
mathematica: f[k_] := Module[{e = If[k == 1, {}, FactorInteger[k][[;; , 2]]]}, If[AllTrue[e, # < 4 &], Count[e, 2], Nothing]]; Array[f, 150]
program: (PARI) list(kmax) = {my(e, is); for(k = 1, kmax, e = factor(k)[, 2]; is = 1; for(i = 1, #e, if(e[i] > 3, is = 0; break)); if(is, print1(#select(x -> x == 2, e), ", "))); }

name: The number of non-unitary prime divisors of the n-th biquadratefree number that is not cubefree.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: f[k_] := If[k == 1, Nothing, Module[{e = FactorInteger[k][[;; , 2]]}, If[Max[e] == 3, Count[e, _?(# > 1 &)], Nothing]]]; Array[f, 1000]
program: (PARI) list(lim) = {my(e); for(k = 2, lim, e = factor(k)[, 2]; if(vecmax(e) == 3, print1(#select(x -> x > 1, e), ", ")));}
author: _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 10 2025

name: The number of non-unitary prime divisors of the n-th biquadratefree number that is not squarefree.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: f[k_] := If[k == 1, Nothing, Module[{e = FactorInteger[k][[;; , 2]]}, If[2 <= Max[e] <= 3, Count[e, _?(# > 1 &)], Nothing]]]; Array[f, 1000]
program: (PARI) list(lim) = {my(e, emax); for(k = 2, lim, e = factor(k)[, 2]; emax = vecmax(e); if(emax > 1 && emax < 4, print1(#select(x -> x > 1, e), ", ")));}
author: _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 10 2025
